    • 枚举常量详细资料

      • ALWAYS

        public static final Option.PkgInfo ALWAYS
        Always generate package-info.class for every package-info.java file. The file may be empty if there annotations with a RetentionPolicy of CLASS or RUNTIME. This option may be useful in conjunction with build systems (such as Ant) that expect javac to generate at least one .class file for every .java file.

      • LEGACY

        public static final Option.PkgInfo LEGACY
        Generate a package-info.class file if package-info.java contains annotations. The file may be empty if all the annotations have a RetentionPolicy of SOURCE. This value is just for backwards compatibility with earlier behavior. Either of the other two values are to be preferred to using this one.

      • NONEMPTY

        public static final Option.PkgInfo NONEMPTY
        Generate a package-info.class file if and only if there are annotations in package-info.java to be written into it.
